Java String to Boolean Example: Boolean.valueOf()
The Boolean.valueOf() method converts string into Boolean object. Let's see the simple code to convert String to Boolean in java.

public class StringToBooleanExample2{
public static void main(String args[]){
String s1="true";  
String s2="TRue";  
String s3="ok";  
Boolean b1=Boolean.valueOf(s1);  
Boolean b2=Boolean.valueOf(s2);  
Boolean b3=Boolean.valueOf(s3);  
System.out.println(b1);  
System.out.println(b2);  
System.out.println(b3);
}}

Test it Now
Output:

true
true
false
